          (Netscape Messaging Server 3.6)  with ESMTP id AAA5F88
          for <td24672@hti.com>; Fri, 17 Sep 1999 11:25:43 -0500
 17 Sep 1999 11:29:15 -0500 (CDT)
Date: Fri, 17 Sep 1999 09:20 -0500 (CDT)
From: "Robert R Mason" <rrmason@hti.com>
Subject: Off Topic! SETI@home


--Boundary_(ID_xeAAaPWf6nWIKjEQC/64dg)
encoding: 7BIT


All,

Sorry for this post, but you may be interested!

If you've got a Piece of Crap (P.C.) or a Unix box sitting idle for long
periods of time; like at work, at night, go to
http://setiathome.ssl.berkeley.edu/, and help in the search for E.T.'s.

Presently they have windoze versions for 95/98/NT and Mac (if you want a
pretty screen saver), and text only versions for UNIX, WinNT, OS/2,
BeOS, Mac OS X Server, OpenVMS (4x (or more!) faster than windoze
versions).

If you do decide to do this, be sure to join the "Amiga Blitz
Programmers" group, under "Clubs" so we can pool our credit!

Again, sorry if your not interested!

Bob Mason

P.S. They have stated that they are working on an Amiga Port. Look out
for it!!

Bob


--Boundary_(ID_xeAAaPWf6nWIKjEQC/64dg)
encoding: 7BIT


