@NODE "Mail_6" "(on topic) preventing window movements"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Sep 1999 18:58:57 -0500
Subject: (on topic) preventing window movements
X-UIDL: e3e07f621e5cdc68d9e5090d751c424d

Hi,

Does anybody know a way to temporarily immobilize a window?

I've tried RTlockWindow, but the window can still be dragged & re-sized.

I also looked for an OS routine to do this, but no luck.  Is there a way?

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



