To unsubscribe, e-mail: blitz-list-unsubscribe@netsoc.ucd.ie
For additional commands, e-mail: blitz-list-help@netsoc.ucd.ie



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_7" "Re: (on topic) preventing window movements"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 02 Sep 1992 12:36:06 +0100
Subject: Re: (on topic) preventing window movements
X-UIDL: 2bb6d2bee137ad918c2b14565364dbe6

Curt Esser churned out *this* drivel:

> Does anybody know a way to temporarily immobilize a window?
 
There's a really hacky way if nothing else : since I know
that you have the window's bitmap and want to block it while
doing calculations, you could clone its position and size,
make a window covering it, non-drag, non-depth arrangeable,
and blit the bitmap into the blocking window :)

See ya,
-- 
