@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_81" "Re: ASM Strings (was something I can't remember)"
From: "David McMinn" <dave@satanicdreams.com>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 5 Oct 1999 09:49:02 +0100
Subject: Re: ASM Strings (was something I can't remember)
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 4d702945ee4c0b8dd61d7c8031e960b6

Hello again,

further to my post yesterday, here's the final piece of information I 
have concerning the use of strings in Blitz Libraries.

The alloc (and copy) string routine has token number $cf01. d0 should 
contain a pointer to the string you want to copy and d1 should 
contain the length of the string. The newly created string is 
returned as a pointer in d0.

The free string routine is token number $cf02. d0 should contain a 
pointer to the string you want to free.

So you'd load up the appropriate parameters (d0/d1 for alloc or d0 
for free) and then ALibJSR $cf0x depending on the routine you want to 
call.


-- 
|) /\ \/ ][ |)   |\/| © |\/| ][ |\| |\|   |   dave@satanicdreams.com
   http://members.xoom.com/David_McMinn   |   ICQ=16827694
