Hi Paul

> I just changed my CV64-3D for a CVPPC. I can't find a way to make BBS
> utilities (RedShapez, RedMapEditor) to appear on a CVPPC screen mode;
> they seem to appear on a standard Amiga screen. Is it possible or I
> have to hack 'em (or is my CVPPC installation finished)?

Both programs have options for configuring the screenmode. However, I 
couldn't get them to work properly here, as I was missing some files.

In the RedShapez, you need to go to the first menu and then 
configure, click on the screenmode button and then select a 
screenmode. After that, go to the first menu, and from the screens 
submenu select "own screen".

The map editor is similar but I think they are in the second/third 
menu.


