@NODE "Mail_98" "Blitting"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Blitting
Date: Wed, 1 Sep 1999 19:36:27 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 25f0df3095577174b7f6846fa9fb6dbd

Hello, ppl

Can anyone explain to me how to use the extended BBlit command that
instructs the blitter which bitplanes to `miss out` for shapes that don`t
use the full palette - I can`t tell if I`m getting them the right way
around - the manual is less than useful.

If, for example, I have a 32 colour palette, but have some shapes that only
use the first 16 colours, what format would the BBlit command take to ensure
that the processor doesn`t bother with the second 16 colours.

Thanks in antici...............pation.

VIC



