@NODE "Mail_114" "Re: BLITZ mode?"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 07 Sep 1999 19:00:12 -0500
Subject: Re: BLITZ mode?
X-UIDL: 4f9b60460cdf82759e33f9cbfc39e654

Hi Sandy

On 07-Sep-99, Sandy Brownlee wrote:
> Hello Again,
> 
> Thanks for your suggestions. It looks like I should use multitasking and
> amigamode. I was intending to make network/ internet support in my game
> eventually, so this was probably the best (only) route to take. I'll
> probably be running on a seperate screen as opposed to WB- is this OK for
> GFX card people? 

Yes, as long as you use a ScreenMode requester to allow them to select a GFX
card screen mode.

Or use BestModeID_ , but that's a whole other can of worms...  

And you must run the program itself in a window (for GFX card modes, I mean)

> i'm not sure how they handle screens and stuff. I also
> just had a look at the Mildred library- now I'm scared. I have not a clue
> where to begin. Looks like I'll be spending a while looking at those
> examples on Blitz-2000.

I just wanted to point out that Freds NCS libraries have some very nice,
easy to use, chunky routines.  It doesn't have anywhere near the
special-effects available in Mildred, but it does contain the most-needed
stuff - ie, the equivalent of normal "blitting" and drawing commands done
to fast-ram chunkies.
As well as C2P conversion.

There is also Mini-Mildred (just the C2P conversion stuff).

Not to mention Blitz's own Chunky.library commands...

Later...
-- 
The Law of Least Astonishment:
The most obvious way of doing something is the correct way.

                                    Yours electronically,
