@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_122" "Re: CD 32 mastering"
Date: Wed, 29 Sep 1999 16:41:40 +0200
From: Kai Gunter Brandt <kai.brandt@cih.uib.no>
Subject: Re: CD 32 mastering
X-UIDL: 9d9764dc8f431c5629bb95c338209f8c

At 04:50 PM 9/29/99 +0200, you wrote:
>Hi gang!
>
>The question is what would I need to create a bootable CD for CD32?
>I have all the CD burners and software for PC...is it possible to make 
>an Amiga CD 32 disk on a PC and make it also bootable (on CD32)
>Any info on that matter is welcome! Thanks!
>

On the PC it's only a file on the CD if i'm not wrong.

Autorun.inf

This file contains things like:
-----------------------------------------
[autorun]
open=Overview\Overvu32.exe
icon=ps4cd.ico
---------------------------------------------

The Amiga have an extra header on the CDinfo track.

I'm i wrong?

So you have to edit some place in the "info"-track.
Kai Gunter Brandt
