@NODE "Mail_123" "Re: CD 32 mastering"
From: Sandy Brownlee <sandy@brownlee99.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Wed, 29 Sep 1999 20:54:28 +0100
Subject: Re: CD 32 mastering
X-UIDL: 55672a2ec72e3eabc28e83c0992026bb

Hello Ott

On 29-Sep-99, you wrote:

> The question is what would I need to create a bootable CD for CD32?
> I have all the CD burners and software for PC...is it possible to make 
> an Amiga CD 32 disk on a PC and make it also bootable (on CD32)
> Any info on that matter is welcome! Thanks!

I have a feeling that the big C, in all their wisdom, made it necessary for
CD32 discs to have a "key track", which was licenced, so that they could
get a cut of any profit made from CD32 games. I'm not sure if it's easy to
get around this.

Regards,

        Sandy Brownlee

-----------------------------
Who else would have a sig like this?


