@NODE "Mail_126" "CD MIXER 1.0"
From: Dimas =?iso-8859-1?Q?Caparr=F3s?= <dcaparros@readysoft.es>
        videotec@vtvm1.cc.vt.edu, PowerUP@lists.best.com
Date: Thu, 16 Sep 1999 15:55:13 +0200
Subject: CD MIXER 1.0
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: e665e4817ca69d0767caaef58c985b69

Sorry, it seems it rebound me, so I will resent it :-(

Hello,

Short:    Prog to mix a number of CDDA files. DEMO
Author:   Dimas Caparrós (dcaparros@readysoft.es)
Uploader: Dimas Caparrós (dcaparros@readysoft.es)
Version:  1.0 demo
Type:     mus/edit

CD MIXER 1.0 DEMO
------------------

This is a utility i wrote for myself. It works here, so it should work at
your home. If enough interest is shown, a 2.0 will be done.

This program takes a number of CDDA files (as the ones generated by MakeCD)
and mix them n seconds, so you can burn "mixed ready" CDs for your pub! :-)

It can create them in separate files (for a DAO writer) or a big superfile
(one track) for TAO writers.

Demo version is limited and fixed for 3 tracks, 20 secs of "mix zone" and
one super track. Registration fee is just 2000 spanish pesetas or 12.02
euros
or $14 US Dollars.

Another prog from me, CDDA2IFF can be found on Aminet. It is a FAST prog to
convert from CDDA (motorola alignement) to AIFF and viceversa, and it is
totally free.

Dimas Caparros
 c/Cedro nş5
 18800 Baza (Granada)
 SPAIN
