Date: Sun, 26 Sep 1999 23:56:01 +0200
Subject: CDDA Mixer 1.1- Faster and unlocked
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: c0fc107b77cd3569c56173e00647ed9d

Hello,

Short:    Prog to mix a number of CDDA files. DEMO
Author:   Dimas Caparrós (dcaparros@readysoft.es)
Uploader: Dimas Caparrós (dcaparros@readysoft.es)
Version:  1.1 demo
Type:     mus/edit
Replaces: CDMix10demo.lha


CD MIXER 1.1 DEMO
------------------

This  is a utility i wrote for myself.  It works here, so it should work at
your home.  If enough interest is shown, a 2.0 will be done.

This program takes a number of CDDA files (as the ones generated by MakeCD)
and  mix  them  n  seconds, so you can burn "mixed ready" CDs for your pub!

It  can create them in separate files (for a DAO writer) or a big superfile
(one track) for TAO writers.

Demo  version is fixed for 3 tracks.  Registration fee is just 2000 spanish
pesetas or 12.02 euros or $14 US Dollars.

1.1:   faster  mix  routines  and  all  options  unlocked; still fixed to 3
tracks.

Another  prog  from me, CDDA2IFF can be found on Aminet.  It is a FAST prog
to convert from CDDA (motorola alignement) to AIFF and viceversa, and it is
totally free.

