@NODE "Mail_181" "Re: DAMN MUI...."
From: Rick Hodger <rick.thehub@bigfoot.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Sep 1999 15:03:30 +0100
Organization: Pagan Software
Subject: Re: DAMN MUI....
X-UIDL: b5d99e9357b099068f3b006b92f1e687

--BOUNDARY.22040824.1

I watched as Rob Hutchinson hammered "DAMN MUI...." out on their keyboard...

>   I`m getting a little sick of MUILists, N and otherwise...
> Attached is a snippet from something I`m working on.

> Can anyone see why having more than 9 entries in
> in this list causes a crash????
> Try removing the "16;" from the line; For A=0 To 16;#TEST_Maximum-1

> It may be something simple that I`m over looking?

I've been following people's problems with NList's and NListviews in the MUI
library for a while now, and after a little experimentation there is a very
simple answer :)

The source for EFMUILib is on Aminet, if you download it, load it into Blitz
and then go down to the very bottom of the file there is a list of classes.
 If you change "List.mui" to "NList.mcc" and "Listview.mui" to
"NListview.mcc", compile it, recreate your deflibs...all your programs when
they use the MUIList and MUIListView commands will automatically use the
NList classes with no problems.

I only thought to try this because after looking at the inludes, I noticed
the tags for MUI's own listview classes and the NList ones were near enough
identical, so why shouldn't the hook in the EFMUIlib work for it as well?

Attached is the altered library.  But please note that if you use this, any
program that used the List.mui and Listview.mui will now automatically use
the NList classes instead.  But please don't ask me for help, the library
still belongs to Erwan Fouret and Andreas Hakansson...I just tweaked it a
bit :) 

