@NODE "Mail_224" "Excessonoff"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Excessonoff
Date: Mon, 20 Sep 1999 18:00:45 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: bd85bdae413afff1823d39f726c1c4ff

Excessonoff

Just for people's information:

I thought that the Excessonoff parameter for the blit commands meant
that blitting would be faster if you were blitting shapes with less
bitplanes than the bitmap to which you were blitting - since there
would be less bitplanes to blit, but this turns out not to be the
case.  Blitting with bitplanes turned off is actually almost half
the speed of normal blitting.

Just thought you might like to know.

VIC E BABES



