@NODE "Mail_225" "Re: Excessonoff"
From: "David McMinn" <dave@satanicdreams.com>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 20 Sep 1999 18:17:07 +0100
Subject: Re: Excessonoff
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: bec878283485dff8628ceacc35f01548

> I thought that the Excessonoff parameter for the blit commands meant
> that blitting would be faster if you were blitting shapes with less
> bitplanes than the bitmap to which you were blitting - since there

Like you found out its slower. But thats cos it does the opposite of 
what you thought (I think). You specify extra planes to blit as 1's, 
so you can create different coloured blits without needing the 
different coloured shapes stored in memory.

So you have a 2 plane shape in memory (4 colours) and you can then 
blit different coloured copies of it by either using the origianl 
version, or one with extra/other bitplanes set to 1.


