@NODE "Mail_232" "Re: Execute_"
 (envelope-from FlameDuck@software.dk)
Date: Sat, 16 Oct 1999 03:59:21 +0200
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <FlameDuck@software.dk>
Subject: Re: Execute_
X-UIDL: 57bb580986c32e860449694edb812e4e

At 11:49 14-10-99 +0000, you wrote:

>cmd$="Run >NIL: prog"
>e=Execute_(&cmd,0,0)

>This works fine, but how do i get the program to display it's ouput
>as normal through it's 'Output Window' without crashing with a msg
>in the window saying something like "Cli [9]" ? any ideas?

Well, first of all you just send the output to CON: instead of NIL:
(cmd$="Run >CON: prog") You can even add other stuff after the CON: bit to
have some more control over it. Or if you're real clever you could "create"
a CON: filehandle and redirect to that using the Execute_ command.

However, It shouldn't crash in either case, simply sending output to NIL:
is not enough to crash any AMiGA I've ever worked with... So there must be
another problem.


/FlameDuck/



@ENDNODE
