@NODE "Mail_254" "Free Code"
From: Tim Herbert <Tim.Herbert@RebusGroup.Com>
Subject: Free Code
Date: Fri, 22 Oct 1999 09:43:03 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
X-UIDL: 1e22a519636ea04fe9f954e49a71f43b

Hi Blitzers,

I've just managed to locate the beginnings of a game I wrote in 1995.

It's a Mario type game (don't tell Nintendo!) called WizWorld. The idea was
that some powerup would turn you into a pointy-hatted Wizard, allowing you
to fire fireballs and destroy blocks with your point hat.
This is currently enabled by pressing one of the buttons on the gamepad.
[Buttons 1 & 2 on the game pad jump and fire - although it'd be easy to
convert to use a regular stick].

Does anyone want the source code to see if they can do anything with it?

Perhaps someone would like to develop it further, the only thing I'd ask is
to be kept up-to-date with any ideas or enhancements. I just ain't got the
time anymore.

Or perhaps somebody may just want to look at it.

The lha is only 92K - I'll email it to anybody who wants it [if loads of
people are interested I'll send it to the list - unless 92K is considered
too big an attachment].

- Tim 'BallBlitz' Herbert



