@NODE "Mail_260" "Re: Free GTList x"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Sep 1999 17:24:36 -0500
Subject: Re: Free GTList x
X-UIDL: 6419d12ac623a2704e358e33718b80e0

--BOUNDARY.1748937592.1

Hi David

On 30-Sep-99, David McMinn wrote:
> 
> 
>> I've created a gadtools list in one of my programs which free's up
>> fine, but the moment I add a GTListView to it, it refuses to free, and
>> spits out a 'Cannot free memory' error. I'm a bit reluctant to give
>> out the code since it's large, and for a project I'm working on.
>> Anyone got any ideas. If not, I'll see if I can recreate the error.
> 
> Running VisualPrefs by any chance? Or any other hack like that? If so 
> you can sort it by either of these two methods:
> 
> Stick in an empty error handler and then remove it afterwards:
> 
> SetErr
> End SetErr
> 
> Free GTList x
> 
> ClrErr
> 
> And I've got a function at home that I can send later, unless someone 
> else has a copy handy. I prefer the function, cos its basically a 
> fixed version of the Free GTList command.

Here it is...
-- 
We all know that no one
understands anything that isn't funny.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748937592.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="freegtlistfix.bb2"
Content-Description: David McMinn <dmcminn@house-of-mojo.freeserve.co.uk>

WBStartup

NEWTYPE.arse
  pad.w
  text.s
End NEWTYPE

NEWTYPE.gtl
  glist.l
  vi.l
  current.l
  windowptr.l
End NEWTYPE

Statement FreeGTList{gt.w}
  *g.gtl = Addr GTList(gt)
  If *g\glist
    FreeGadgets_ *g\glist
    *g\glist = 0
    FreeVisualInfo_ *g\vi
  End If
End Statement

Dim List test.arse(100)
While AddItem(test())
  test()\text = String$(Chr$(Rnd(26)+65),10)
Wend

WbToScreen 0
AddIDCMP #LISTVIEWIDCMP
Window 0,0,0,320,200,$100f,"AAA",-1,-1
GTListView 0,0,10,10,290,170,"",0,test()

AttachGTList 0,0

While WaitEvent<>$200
Wend

DetachGTList 0
;seterr:end seterr
;Free GTList 0
;clrerr
FreeGTList{0}
End




