@NODE "Mail_265" "Freeing bsdsocket.library"
From: Roger Light <roger@mindless.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Sep 1999 09:17:41 GMT
Subject: Freeing bsdsocket.library
X-UIDL: 1a10df712a8a5376eb943a7584ca99aa
Status: U

Hi all,

When my program starts, it automatically tries to open all of the libraries
that it needs. This is, I guess, the way that Blitz handles libraries
because I have nothing to do with it ;) One of these libraries is
bsdsocket.library, which is only present if Miami/Genesis/AmiTCP etc. are
running. The trouble is, if I then try and quit Miami (in my case) then it
complains my program is still using it's libraries and won't release them.

Has anybody any idea how I can get around this?

Cheers,

Roger
