@NODE "Mail_275" "Re: Freeing bsdsocket.library"
Date: Sun, 03 Oct 1999 20:42:50 +0100
From: Paul Burkey <burkey@bigfoot.com>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Freeing bsdsocket.library
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 4d536d4a6299c3def68eb7d3ab2f1827

Roger Light wrote:
> I've attached a little demo/bastardisation of the assemblified
> TCPFuncs. It should create a file ram:yahoo.html which is the yahoo
> index page. It only uses a few of the TCPFuncs functions, I'm going
> to convert TCPFuncs completely if that's OK with Paul...

Sure, feel free to copy/use/rewrite and redistribute the TCPFuncs
code however you wish. I originaly wrote them as an expected future
part of Foundation but the TCP support of Foundation was canceled
when I decided to design the sequel (Foundation's Edge) totaly around
a multiplyaer design rather than simply a TCP add-on. The new game
is actually coded in C++, So I never really managed to utilize those
functions after all! 

> Question - Do I always need to store a4-a6 even if I'm not using
> them? I suppose I need to assume that something else in the
> bsdsocket function might change them. Is that right?

I don't think you do, No.

Cheers,

Paul

