@NODE "Mail_307" "GTCalc (was Rounding amounts)"
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 21 Sep 99 13:36:34 +1000
Subject: GTCalc (was Rounding amounts)
X-UIDL: 08e2fb43df8c1ba4ef813acbc943de3a

--=_=8<==MD237E789E2-10BF4059==8<=_=
Encoding: 7bit

Thanks to everyone who gave suggestions for the rounding to 5 cents
problem.    It now works fine.

This all started because I needed to enter a series of money amounts
in a GTString (i.e 2.55+1.33+25.71, rather than just entering the
total amount).    Then, having developed the code for that, I
remembered that someone suggested a GTCalc gadget.   I've attached my
function to do this sum as a starting point.    It doesn't  do any
more than addition, but it may serve as a trigger for someone who
needs a more complex version.

Anyway, enjoy it or not as you wish

Cheers

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+8Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

--=_=8<==MD237E789E2-10BF4059==8<=_=
Encoding: plain (7/8 bit)
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="GTCalc.asc"
X-MD2-FilePath: Blitz2:Examples/GTCalc.asc

;  Elmentary GTCalc function
;  Author:  Tony Rolfe   edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au
;  Status:  Freeware, do whatever you want with it
;  Purpose: Takes a string entered into a GTString gadget and interprets it
;           as an addition sum of money values.
;           The following are valid:
;              25
;              12.23+1.2+5+36547.99+.9+
;
;           The following are invalid:
;              2.5.6    ; two Dec points in one number
;              2 + 2    ; embedded spaces
;              2.345    ; three decimal places
;
;
;  It should be easy to allow subtraction
;  If anyone modifies it handle a full set of mathematical functions
;  I'd love a copy.

Function.l GTCalc{Next_ID.b}  ; Ignore the Next_ID, it's part of my
                              ; data validation suite

SHARED all_valid     ; Flag used to report data entry errors
SHARED GadList       ; Current GTList number

; First, pull in what the user entered
;
a$=StripLead$(StripTrail$(GTGetString(GadList,GadgetHit),32),32)

If Right$(a$,1) <> "+"  ; Add a trailing plus sign if needed
   a$ + "+"
EndIf

all_valid    = #True_Flag     ; So far so good
a.l          = 0              ; Set total to zero
b.l          = 0              ; also intermediate result
DecimalHit.b = #False_Flag    ; Not yet hit the decimal point
Places.w     = 0              ; No decimal places yet

For i.b = 1 To Len(a$)                       ; Take each character in turn
   j.b = Instr("0123456789.+",Mid$(a$,i,1))  ; Is it valid?
   If j = 0                                  ; No
      all_valid = #False_Flag                ; ... so tell someone
      i = Len(a$)                            ; ... and terminate the loop
   Else
      If j < 11                              ; Was it a numeric digit
         b = (b * 10) + j - 1                ; Calculate intermediate result
         Places + 1                          ; Increment decimal places
      Else
         If j = 11                           ; Was it a decimal point?
            If DecimalHit                    ; Yes, so was there one before?
               all_valid = #False_Flag       ; Yes - invalid entry
               i = Len(a$)                   ; ... so terminate the loop
            Else
               DecimalHit = #True_Flag       ; First Decimal Point hit
               Places.w   = 0                ; ... so reset decimal place counter
            EndIf
         Else
            If DecimalHit                    ; Must be a plus sign
               Select Places                 ; ... so finalise number
                  Case 0                     ; No DP entered
                     b * 100                 ; ... so multiply by 100
                  Case 1                     ; One DP entered
                     b * 10                  ; ... so multiply by 10
                  Case 2                     ; Two DP entered, so leave alone
                  Default                    ; Three or more DP
                     all_valid = #False_Flag ; ... so invalid
                     i = Len(a$)             ; ... and terminate loop
               End Select
            Else                             ; No Decimal point entered
               b * 100                       ; ... so multiply by 100
            EndIf
            a + b                            ; Add intermediate to total
            b = 0                            ; reset intermediate,
            DecimalHit = #False_Flag         ; ... Decimal point Flag
            Places = 0                       ; ... and Decimal places counter
         EndIf
      EndIf
   EndIf
Next                                         ; Go get next character
;
; Ignore this, it's part of my data validation suite
;
;Exit_Validation{Next_ID,"Invalid Currency Calculation"}

Function Return a

End Function



--=_=8<==MD237E789E2-10BF4059==8<=_=

