Hi,

Full of problems recently aren't I? :) Here's my latest. Why is it, that when
I'm trying to font sensitise (??) one of my programs, the GTGadgets don't work
well at all. I mean, I've got a program which I just started, which puts a
GTString on the screen. It works fine if I haven't loaded in any other fonts
(using LoadFont) and called them using WindowFont, but if I actually try to
use a different font to the default Topaz, then only the label of the GTString
is shown, and the actual gadget does not appear. Nor does it appear if I don't
issue a label.

I'm positive it used to work (definately with the Peridot, 7 font anyway). The
font I'm trying to use is Helvetica, 13. Do you want example code?

Help! (Again)

Neil

