@NODE "Mail_314" "Re: GTGadget problems (plus new problem)"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Sep 1999 08:49:35 -0500
Subject: Re: GTGadget problems (plus new problem)
X-UIDL: 08ecb68d2ab2c32ed6e2ee2a286b527e

--BOUNDARY.1748157544.1

Hi Neil

On 26-Sep-99, Neil Bullock wrote:

> Anyway, since the original message was about problems making a GUI font
> sensitive, I have another question. Does someone have a simple equation to
> work out how high a window should be?

I don't know how simple this is, but I've attached some code I use to make a
window font sensitive.  It takes into account the sizes the window borders
will be (thanks to David McMinn), the size of the font, the longest line of
gadget text's length, and an adjustable spacing between gadgets.

This should give you some ideas, anyway.  You'll need amigalibs.res.

Later...
-- 
Be friends with the wolf, but keep one hand on your ax.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748157544.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="FontSens.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable

*scr.Screen     =3D Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
diswid.w        =3D *scr\Width
dishit.w        =3D *scr\Height
disdep.w        =3D *scr\BitMap\Depth
botnosize.w     =3D *scr\WBorBottom
numcols.w       =3D 2^disdep

winbot.w =3D 10  ;fallback value in case this next bit fails

*dri.DrawInfo =3D GetScreenDrawInfo_(*scr)

If *dri
  If (*scr\Flags & #SCREENHIRES)
    sis.l=3D#SYSISIZE_MEDRES
  Else
    sis=3D#SYSISIZE_LOWRES
  EndIf
  Dim tags.TagItem(4)
  tags(0)\ti_Tag =3D #SYSIA_DrawInfo,*dri
  tags(1)\ti_Tag =3D #SYSIA_Which,#SIZEIMAGE
  tags(2)\ti_Tag =3D #SYSIA_Size,sis
  tags(3)\ti_Tag =3D #TAG_DONE
  *img.Image =3D NewObjectA_(0,"sysiclass",&tags(0))
  If *img
    winbot.w=3D *img\Height
    DisposeObject_ *img
  End If
  FreeScreenDrawInfo_ *scr,*dri
EndIf

winleft.w =3D*scr\WBorLeft
wintop.w  =3D*scr\WBorTop+*scr\Font\ta_YSize+1
winright.w=3D*scr\WBorRight


winxpad.w=3Dwinleft+winright
winypad.w=3Dwintop+winbot
stdypad.w=3Dwintop+botnosize

picmaxX.w=3Ddiswid-winxpad
picmaxY.w=3Ddishit-winypad

font$=3DPeek$ (*scr\Font\ta_Name) ;screen font's name
fontY.w=3D*scr\Font\ta_YSize      ;font height

LoadFont 0,font$,fontY


MenusOff
slideflag.b=3D1
#X=3D1
#Y=3D2

; set up the Image Scaling Window

=2EImageWindow

#prop    =3D 0
#xdivide =3D 1
#doublex =3D 2
#ydivide =3D 3
#doubley =3D 4
#width   =3D 5
#height  =3D 6
#load    =3D 7
#save    =3D 8
#undo    =3D 9
#rest    =3D10
#half    =3D11
#double  =3D12

temp$=3D"MMDoubleMM"
Gwide.w=3DTextLength_ (*scr\RastPort,&temp$,Len(temp$))
Ghigh.w=3DfontY+2
Gspace.w=3D2

Win1wide.w=3Dwinxpad+Gwide*3+Gspace*5

Gx1.w=3DGspace
Gx2.w=3DGspace*2+Gwide
Gx3.w=3DGspace*3+Gwide*2
Sld.w=3DGwide*3+Gspace


Gy.w=3DGspace

GTTags #GTNM_Clipped,-1,#GTTX_Justification,#GTJ_CENTER
GTText      1,#width,  Gx1,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Width",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,"(x)"

GTTags #GTNM_Clipped,-1,#GTTX_Justification,#GTJ_CENTER
GTText      1,#height ,Gx3,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Height",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,"(y)"=


Gy+Ghigh+Gspace

GTButton    1,#undo,   Gx2,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Undo",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40

Gy+Ghigh+Gspace

GTButton    1,#xdivide,Gx1,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Half",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40
GTButton    1,#half,   Gx2,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Half",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40
GTButton    1,#ydivide,Gx3,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Half",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40

Gy+Ghigh+Gspace

GTButton    1,#doublex,Gx1,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Double",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40
GTButton    1,#double, Gx2,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Double",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40
GTButton    1,#doubley,Gx3,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Double",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40

Gy+Ghigh+Gspace

GTSlider    1,#prop,Gx1,Gy,Sld,Ghigh,"",#PLACETEXT_BELOW|$40|$80,40,picma=
xX

Gy+Ghigh+Gspace

GTButton    1,#load,   Gx1,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Load",#PLACETEXT_IN
GTButton    1,#rest,   Gx2,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Restore",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40
GTButton    1,#save,   Gx3,Gy,Gwide,Ghigh,"Save",#PLACETEXT_IN|$40

Gy+Ghigh+Gspace+stdypad
Win1high.w=3DGy

AddIDCMP $10
Window 1,diswid-Win1wide,dishit-Win1high,Win1wide,Win1high,$1000|$2|$4|$8=
," Ready...",-1,-1
CatchDosErrs
AttachGTList 1,1



--BOUNDARY.1748157544.1

