Encoding: 7bit

On Sun, 26 Sep 1999 16:38:35 +0100 Roman Schaub said:
> Hello 
> 
> When i set up a gtlist containing some gtinteger gadgets, everything runs
> fine, except that you cannot enter numbers like 10.5 .You are only allowed
> to enter rounded values
> (only real numbers as 1 2 3 4 5 6 etc.)
> How can i override this limitation?
I always use GTString's for all input, regardless of content and then
validate the text according to whatever is supposed to go into the
gadgets.

The attached function validates money amounts so it accepts two
decimal places (actually allows a lot of money amounts added
together).

Ignore the Exit_Validation{} at the end and the NextID at the front.

Use it in the main loop like
ev = waitevent
   if ev = #IDCMP_GADGETUP
      select GadgetHit
          case #NumberGadget
             Amount.l = Validate_Money{#AnotherGadget}
          case something else
     end select
  end if


Hope it helps

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+8Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

--=_=8<==MD237EF5C2F-421D3E07==8<=_=
