@NODE "Mail_320" "GTText gadgets"
From: Matt Briggs <engine9@ukonline.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 09 Sep 1999 15:50:29 +0000
X-SenderInfo: 1; picture="http://www.enginenine.cjb.net/gfx/logo001.gif"
Organization: Engine Nine Design
Subject: GTText gadgets
X-UIDL: 250b3439d2e09f04a01987faa6ebd66e

HiYa all

 I am using a GTText gadget to display some text in a
window, and I am using flag $10 to centre the text, like
so:-

> GTText 0,1,x,y,w,h,"CENTER!!!",$10,""

 However when I use GTSetString to modify the text inside
the GTText object, it is left aligned and not centered like
I want it to be. 

> GTSetString 0,1,"CENTER!!!"

Can anyone help? Or does anyone have any other ways of doing
easy text display in a border? Ta very much :)

-- 
Massive regards
M@t Briggs

