@NODE "Mail_329" "Re: GTText gadgets"
Date: Sun, 19 Sep 1999 11:01:30 +0200
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <FlameDuck@software.dk>
Subject: Re: GTText gadgets
X-UIDL: ae97a91ec314b7e2b73aa84231f847b5

At 09:12 18-09-99 +0100, you wrote:

>> *This shouldn't be bold*, *but* *this* *should*

>It appears both bold. And heres why. ANYTHING enclosed within *'s is bold,
not
>just singular words. THis is mentioned in the YAM docs. 

No, but according to the standards, (I can't remember which, it's ANSI
something) it's only *supposed* to be single words, it's not tags like in
HTML, the reason is that otherwise text will get distorted... Check this out :

"You then have to connect wire #2 with the pin labeled _GND+ and solder the
green wire onto the 555 timer circuit"

Okay, so now after this breif electronics statement everything is totally
fucked up. In YAM. Load the message into SPOT or THOR or another program
that UNDERSTANDS the standard, and you'll see the above text correctly (or
turn of text styles)

And BTW in case you're curious, Eudora doesn't support text styles.


/FlameDuck/


