@NODE "Mail_333" "HAM sandwich"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 05 Sep 1999 19:41:21 +0100
Subject: HAM sandwich
X-UIDL: a70d907a4ba1c32e9b9041f618093991

--BOUNDARY.1748185128.1

Hi all, 

I've just spent this afternoon messing around with image.library,
which is a great little library that deals with image remapping,
scaling and stuff like that, but best of all, it lets you display
images properly on *HAM6/8* screens (well, I've never seen any Blitz
source for this ;)

If anyone wants a copy (around 100k), let me know...

(See attached for a crap HAM demo, but make sure you put
image.library into LIBS: first!)

See ya,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

But what is all this fear of and opposition to oblivion? What
is the matter with the soft darkness, the dreamless sleep?
-- James Thurber

--BOUNDARY.1748185128.1
