@NODE "Mail_337" "help converting C loop to Blitz loop"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@ukonline.co.uk>
Date: Thu, 21 Oct 1999 01:25:07 +0000
Subject: help converting C loop to Blitz loop
Encoding: binary
X-UIDL: 077118b5c4de26fecc080ff10a92eb91

Hello,

Can anyone with experience of C tell me the correct way of converting the
following code, I'll include what I've done(probably way out).

C-Code:-

                  /* Copy color tables... */
                  for( i = 0UL ; i < numcolors ; i++ )
                  {
                    dcregs[ ((i * 3) + 0) ] = scregs[ ((i * 3) + 0) ]; /* copy r, */
                    dcregs[ ((i * 3) + 1) ] = scregs[ ((i * 3) + 1) ]; /*      g, */
                    dcregs[ ((i * 3) + 2) ] = scregs[ ((i * 3) + 2) ]; /*      b  */

                    *dcm++ = *scm++; /* copy colorregisters */
                  }


My Blitz code
; Not sure whether this is correct
          Dim cols.b(numcolors,2)
          If *dcregs AND *dcm
            For i=0 To numcols
              j.l=i*12 : j+*scregs
              k.l=i*12 : k+*dcregs
              r.l=Peek.b(j  ) MOD 256
              g.l=Peek.b(j+4) MOD 256
              b.l=Peek.b(j+8) MOD 256
              Poke.b k,r : Poke.b k+4,g : Poke.b k+8,b
              *scma.ColorRegister=*scm+i
              cols(i,0)=*scma\red : cols(0,1)=*scma\green : cols(i,2)=*scma\blue
            Next i
            *dcm=&cols(0,0)
          End If

Use experience to get any missing definitons as this is from the middle of a
routine I'm working on.

Cya,

    Leigh.

-- 

 A1200T - 040-33Mhz +16MbFast - 3.2Gig HD - 32x CD - ZIP

 EMail: mailto:lparry@ukonline.co.uk
 URL: http://web.ukonline.co.uk/lparry/

 Be alert - your country needs lerts.



@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_338" "Re: help converting C loop to Blitz loop"
Sender: y0014694@rzcomm4.rz.tu-bs.de
Date: Thu, 28 Oct 1999 17:54:38 +0200
From: Roger Light <rogerlight@mindless.com>
Organization: TU-Braunschweig, Rechenzentrum
Subject: Re: help converting C loop to Blitz loop
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: b5c29a3681038888c6bfa1723f90ccc4

Leigh Parry wrote:

> for( i = 0UL ; i < numcolors ; i++ )

> For i=0 To numcols

I'm not sure about the rest of it, but can suggest a change for the
above. 

The 'i<numcolors' bit means that the loop should keep going whilst that
is true. This means that your for loop should be for i=0 to numcols-1

Regards,

Roger

