@NODE "Mail_346" "hi-lo res"
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: hi-lo res
Date: Fri, 1 Oct 1999 18:27:59 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: da80a08dd01175f4771cb74cd48f467c

I`ve been playing Pinball Illusions quite a lot lately - anyone who has
played it will know that you can switch between high and low res by pressing
F9/10.  I was wondering if this was possible in Blitz.  I would have thought
that you would first have to free the current display, which would dump you
back to workbench, before creating the new.  Anyone know?

VIC



