--BOUNDARY.1748401728.2

Neil Bullock churned out *this* drivel:

> Excuse the bizzare subject. Right, how would I go about working out how
> many bytes a certain number of blocks takes up?

See attached - cut out all of the NPrint lines except the Extra! Extra! one
for your bytes per block...

It's 512 here, but you can't assume that...

See ya,
-- 
<tsb>
<sb>James L Boyd - jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk
<sb>Member of Team *AMIGA*, and *Dogbert's New Ruling Class.*
<sb>Connected from Dundee, Scotland. 
<sb>(http://surf.to/all-hail/)
<tsb>

But what is all this fear of and opposition to oblivion? What
is the matter with the soft darkness, the dreamless sleep?
-- James Thurber

--BOUNDARY.1748401728.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="info.asc"
Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Description: Bytes per block and more

Function.f Percent {outof.f,total.f}
  ans.f=3D100*(outof/total)
Function Return ans
End Function

d$=3D"Sys:"

lock.l=3DLock_(&d$,#MODE_OLDFILE)

If lock

  DEFTYPE.InfoData id

  If Info_(lock,&id)

    NPrint "Disk information for ",d$
    NPrint ""
    NPrint "Disk size   : ",id\id_NumBlocks*id\id_BytesPerBlock," bytes"
    Print "In use      : ",id\id_NumBlocksUsed*id\id_BytesPerBlock," byte=
s"
    NPrint " (",Percent {id\id_NumBlocksUsed*id\id_BytesPerBlock,id\id_Nu=
mBlocks*id\id_BytesPerBlock},"% full)"
    Print  "Disk state  : "

    Select id\id_DiskState
      Case #ID_WRITE_PROTECTED
        NPrint "Disk is write-protected"
      Case #ID_VALIDATING
        NPrint "Disk is validating"
      Case #ID_VALIDATED
        NPrint "Disk is OK!"
    End Select

    NPrint "Soft errors : ",id\id_NumSoftErrors

    Print  "Disk type   : "

    Select id\id_DiskType
      Case #ID_NO_DISK_PRESENT
        NPrint "Disk not present"
      Case #ID_UNREADABLE_DISK
        NPrint "Disk unreadable/corrupt"
      Case #ID_DOS_DISK
        NPrint "OFS disk"
      Case #ID_FFS_DISK
        NPrint "FFS disk"
      Case #ID_INTER_DOS_DISK
        NPrint "International OFS disk"
      Case #ID_INTER_FFS_DISK
        NPrint "International FFS disk"
      Case #ID_FASTDIR_DOS_DISK
        NPrint "Diskcached OFS disk"
      Case #ID_FASTDIR_FFS_DISK
        NPrint "Diskcached FFS disk"
      Case #ID_NOT_REALLY_DOS
        NPrint "Non-DOS disk"
      Case #ID_KICKSTART_DISK
        NPrint "Kickstart disk"
      Case #ID_MSDOS_DISK
        NPrint "MS-DOS disk"
    End Select

  NPrint "":NPrint "Extra! Extra! Bytes per block : ",id\id_BytesPerBlock=


  EndIf

UnLock_ lock

Else End
EndIf

MouseWait
End

--BOUNDARY.1748401728.2--




