Hi SALLIN

On 10-Oct-99, SALLIN Nicolas wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> I have got a crash during the downloading of my mails. And, thanx to the
> copyback of PFS2, they are erased from the pop3 server but not stored on
> my hard drive. And I haven't read them, of course. So, I need a way to get
> them. I can at least get back the msg from this ML, if not my personal
> mails... (*grglgloumpfl* PFS...)
> 
> In the message sent by the ML server, there are all the infos to get some
> past post. But they need to be referenced by a number, as "post 1439 to
> 1498", you see. How can I know this number ?

If you look at the full header for the email, you will find that the ones
sent to you from the Blitz-list start with:

<blitz-list-return-

followed by a number.  In the case of your posting, for example, the number
was 14626

A mail from the list a few days ago had:
14612

So, to get the most recent 20 letters from the Blitz-list, you could ask for
14605 - 14626.


Unfortunately, to get a particular email's number you would need to have
that email...

But then, you wouldn't need to get it, would you...   ;)

> Thanx for any help !

Well, not much help, I'm afraid.  But that's all I know about it. 

Later...
-- 

