@NODE "Mail_401" "Re: Locking and UnLocking"
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Sat, 02 Oct 1999 17:55:58 +0100
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Locking and UnLocking
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: ebfe1f47b669c52a45ce27ae902be7f0

Neil Bullock wrote:

> Hi,
>
> How do you use Lock_() and UnLock_() to lock files 'n' dirs?

Ok, an example:

*MyLock.l = Lock_("FileName",#ACCESS_READ)
If *MyLock
    NPrint "FileName locked"
    UnLock_ *Mylock
else
    NPrint "Can't lock file"
endif

There are other tags depending on what you want to do to a file:

#ACCESS_READ allows you to read a file.  More than one program can read a file
at once.
#ACCESS_WRITE allows you to write to a file and is exclusive - no other
program may lock the file (either read or write)

You will of course need amigalibs.res for these constants.

    Thom


