@NODE "Mail_413" "Mischievous GTText"
From: Roger Light <roger@mindless.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Sep 1999 17:05:06 GMT
Subject: Mischievous GTText
X-UIDL: dedeaef951171291197bfb318e49ba2c

--BOUNDARY.1747126704.1

Hi all,

I've got an intriguing little problem. Well it's no real problem, but I'm
curious as to what causes it ;)

Attached is some code that demonstrates it. If you run it and then open
Exchange. In exchange, select Test then hide and show the interface. Notice
how the text gadget remains unchanged? Now click on the Change button and
hide and show the interface as before. The text gadget should have changed
to the window title. 

Any ideas what causes this?

Cheers,

Roger
-- 
IRC: oojah @ Arcnet | ICQ: 9727627
-------------------
UK University Email Search - Find undergraduate email addresses!
http://start.at/uksearch
-------------------
GetCDDB Support Page
http://www.angelfire.com/vt/ralight/getcddb.html
--BOUNDARY.1747126704.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="texttest.asc"

#_STATUS_TEXT = 50
#_CHANGE_BUTTON = 51

WBStartup

LoadFont 0,"XEN.font",8
Use IntuiFont 0
FindScreen 0

If NOT MakeCommodity("Test","Test Program","Watch the stupid text gadget")
  End
EndIf

GTText 0,#_STATUS_TEXT,80,10,95,15,"",0,"Hello"
GTButton 0,#_CHANGE_BUTTON,15,10,50,15,"Change",$10

Gosub OpenWindow

Repeat
  Wait
  winEvent.l=Event
  CXmsg.l=CommodityEvent

  If CXmsg.l ; exchange message
    Gosub HandleCX
  EndIf
  If winEvent.l
    Gosub HandleIDCMP
  EndIf
Until winEvent=$200

End

.HandleIDCMP
If winEvent=$40
  If GadgetHit=#_CHANGE_BUTTON
    GTSetString 0,#_STATUS_TEXT,"Changed"
  EndIf
EndIf

Return

.OpenWindow
  DefaultIDCMP $40|$200
  Window 0,10,15,200,50,$20100e,"Truely Bizarre",0,1
  AttachGTList 0,0
winopen.b=True
Return

.CloseWin
  Free Window 0
  DetachGTList 0
  winopen.b=False
Return

;-------------------------
; Below is just the code to act on Show/Hide from Exchange

.HandleCX
Select ExchangeMessage

  Case CxAppear
    If winopen.b=False
      Gosub OpenWindow
    EndIf

  Case CxDisAppear
    If winopen.b=True
      Gosub CloseWin
    EndIf
End Select
Return




--BOUNDARY.1747126704.1

