On 18-Oct-99, Mikkel Lřkke wrote:
C=At 03:07 16-10-99 PDT, you wrote:

C=>Does anybody have a good MOD-player library for Blitz Basic? It should be 
C=>player what can play CIA-timed modules etc.

C=AFAIK, the EML library (or something) off Aminet can do that just fine,
C=unfortunately the one I have crashes if something else is using the audio
C=hardware, and is a bit shakey on a 040... As an alternative you can use the
C=DBM player routines done by someone on this list, can't remember who, I've
C=lost all the mails sent to my AMiGA.

The EML sucks. Yes it crashes when something else wants to access the audio,
like if I start quakeppc and forget to quit my player. It also has random
crashes which do or don`t have something to do with interaction with
another program. It has problems with speed every now and then. There`s no
function to free a module, if you just load another over it you can have
weird sound hickups coming thru every now and then. Just load a non
existing file in place to free. 

For proper modplaying use the xbciatracker library(this one is the newest
version). The DBM library only plays digibooster songs.

Regards

