@NODE "Mail_475" "Re: Mui NList Hook Example Here !!"
From: Rob Hutchinson <rob@satanicdreams.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Sep 1999 20:07:06 +0100
X-SenderInfo: 1; homepage="http://www.satanicdreams.com/"; dob=19071981
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: Mui NList Hook Example Here !!
X-UIDL: 517d19477e43a09fa8e3a38cf79d77da

--BOUNDARY.274316440.1

Hello jean
> Hi everyone,
> 
>    Here is my latest program. I've try to open multi-column with hook
> function.  

This is great, it`s what we need.. The list implementation in the EFMUILib
sucks!.. I`ve been trying to get NLists working properly for AGES... And
I failed.

>    I used allocvec_ for create an entry, but when the Pointer (*toto in
> the program) was send to the Display statement, i losed the strings. 
> so, i used allocvec_ for store the strings, and used their pointers
> in the entry newtype (*toto)

No, it`s not very stable at all, every time I quit it fries all other
programs running >:/

>    If anyone know how to make a newtype who store a string ans not a
> pointer of strings , then email me please ..

Well, I had problems opening a single column NList and making it
add, delete etc etc.. Though it might have been cos I was using that
sourcearray tag. It was easy to add entires in the list, it was just
hard to modify them without deleting and re-inserting them.
This was a single column list aswell, not half as hard as a Multi
column list.

I even resorted to creating my own String array... As every time
I typed more then 5 letters in into the list it corrupted.
I opened a memory area of Entries*Entry_Length and each
entry was a constant length, and always located at the same location
in memory.. But it still cocked up... So i gave up.

I really think we need to get these NLists working in Blitz.
Attached is a cleaner version of the source, I`ve changed a few
minor things too.. I was trying to get it to dynamically alter data
when you enter it in the string... But without much luck..
but then I`m not ACTUALLY sure of the correct procedure for
dynamically altering data in a list.. I`m not even sure if NList
stores it`s own data when you pass strings to it?? Does it
take those strings and stick them in it`s own memory area?
If so, how do you alter them?

See attached anyways. :).. Shame it`s so unstable :(
Please let me know if you get any of this working.

>   
> 
-- 

Rob,
