@NODE "Mail_477" "My first post and my first question !"
From: Blitz list <Henes.TSK@iName.com>
Date: Tue, 05 Oct 1999 21:11:35 +0200
Organization: Taskers
Subject: My first post and my first question !
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 6e25f4a0c4d51ff4dfe5079eaeaccf68

Hello,

I have subscribed to the list yesterday.
I read the Aminet's BlitzList archives since many years, so it's like if I
know each of you... :-)

About myself:
    - I'm french, my english is ugly and I'm a student in computing (sadly, it's
       less interesting that Blitz coding...).
    - I have an A1200/BlizzPPC@200/SCSI/BVision/64Mo and a Mikronik tower with a 
       blocking keyboard interface :-/

OffTopic: My reseller tell me that Mikronik stops his activitie... any info ?

And now, the most interesting:
I have contacted "TheFarm" and they have accepted to give me the "Roketz"
game source code. BTW, this is the first time I announce publicly this new...
I will post more infos about this, later (except if nobody is interested !)


OK, my question now:

Some custom libs used by Roketz are written in asm.
For a true assembler, not the Blitz inlined one !
I didn't this was possible...
And of course, I can't get them compiled.
The Farm (hello Ott, I know you read the list !) has send some already compiled
lib, but because of that, I can't make any change to them, of course.

Any help will be greatly received...

Ciao

NB1: Many months ago, I have stopped all communication with you, James L Boyd.
        I'm sorry. I had lost my account...

NB2: Mathias, I have see that you have requested the MarkSilby's adresse,
        funny ! But thanx !
-- 
Nicolas SALLIN, aka Henes/Taskers
Roketz developer
