@NODE "Mail_483" "My opinion about Pure Basic"
From: Dimas =?iso-8859-1?Q?Caparr=F3s?= <dcaparros@readysoft.es>
Date: Fri, 24 Sep 1999 15:31:44 +0200
Subject: My opinion about Pure Basic
X-UIDL: 8a12775c18d6fa5f6db368b508815598

Hello,

About PureBasic... well, it could be good, but now, I will not spend a penny
for it... why?

-Improper guide.
 Where is explained the PRINT (and related) commands? it is in the examples
of other commands, but not himslef...

-INPUT missed?
 Sure, it has to have it, but no reference for such a command anywhere...

-Can ASM be included?
 If so, where is explained?

-How to access OS routines?
 If there is a way, we could start using some non purebasic implemented
routines, or external libraries, but no luck also here... Try to reserve
some memory? You can not.

-External Editor
 It is in the way, but nobody will pay for a "future" feature, and not such
much money. They must begin asking money when the product is finished, not
before. Will I pay and later, the programmer go to PC world and forgive me?
Although Blitz is no more, at least it is "finished" :-)

+Good Things: PPC support
 As soon as I get something as Mildred implemented for PuerBasic, I will
pay; PPC is great!

+System compliant
 I do not need direct hardware access. Of course, it is good, but to do it,
you can use Blitz, even best, AmosPRO :-)

Kind regards


