Hi amorel

On 29-Sep-99, amorel wrote:
> Why is it with naslrequest and ntaglist that if I try to do a naddtag
> #ASLFR_TitleText that the title appears in the drawer gadget too? The
> #ASLFR_TitleDrawer (or what was the exact spelling) just doesnt work then.
> A known bug? Afaik its a bug and am I doing everything right. Cause if I
> leave out #ASLFR_TitleText all goes well.

I'm not sure if this will help with Naslrequest, but I find when making
taglists for system functions it is better to do this with strings:

Title$="Select a file"
#ASLFR_TitleText,&Title$


Instead of:

#ASLFR_TitleText,"Select a file"

Later...
