@NODE "Mail_491" "Re: Naslrequest"
From: amorel <amorel@xs4all.nl>
Date: Mon, 04 Oct 1999 18:58:47 +0500
Subject: Re: Naslrequest
X-UIDL: 296956120e0e6e80914d419f41882a5a

On 04-Oct-99, Thomas Cobb wrote:

C=Actually, it's your fault and not a bug =)

Ah, so thats why the example does the same thing as I do(look at the
aslscreenrequest Naddtags)?

C=functions that take a string as an argument what you actually pass is a
C=pointer to a string. 

Well, I find that silly =) Anyway, it works now thanks. Btw, why is there
a & before the variable, I thought a * shows a pointer. Or can one use
both?


; *********************************************************
;                   New ASL Library
;    Coded by AlphaSOUND - (c) 1998 Fantaisie software
; *********************************************************

; *********************************************************
;                     Example 1
;    Open the 3 ASL requesters one after other
; *********************************************************

; *********************************************************
;                     Begin INIT
; *********************************************************
;
;
; 31/01/1999
;   Use new taglist system.
;   Use NPeek$()

WBStartup

; Be sure to do ALL the Init stuff before try to END your
; program, else it will crash.
;
a.l = NInitASL

If a = 0
  NPrint "I Can't open the ASL.library V36+ !"
  NPrint "Bye bye..."
  NMouseWait
  End
EndIf

TagList.l = NInitTagList(10)


; *********************************************************
;            Start with the ASL file requester...
; *********************************************************

SelectedFile$ = NASLFileRequest(0)  ; Look, I use the default ASL setting.
Very quick ;-)

If SelectedFile$
  NPrint "File selected : ", SelectedFile$
  NPrint "Position and Size of the requester when quitting : "
  NPrint "Pos: (", NASLPosX, ",", NASLPosY, ") Size: ", NASLWidth, "*",
NASLHeight
Else
  NPrint "ASL File Requester cancelled."
EndIf


; *********************************************************
;             ...Followed by the FontRequester...
; *********************************************************

NResetTagList #ASLFO_InitialTopEdge , 14
      NAddTag #ASLFO_InitialLeftEdge, 20
      NAddTag #ASLFO_InitialWidth   , 400
      NAddTag #ASLFO_InitialName    , "topaz.font"
      NAddTag #ASLFO_InitialSize    , 11
      NAddTag #ASLFO_DoStyle        , 1
      NAddTag #ASLFO_FixedWidthOnly , 1
      NAddTag #ASLFO_DoFrontPen     , 1
      NAddTag #ASLFO_DoBackPen      , 1
      NAddTag #ASLFO_TitleText      ,"Blitz II Rulez"

*a.NFontInfo = NASLFontRequest(TagList)

If *a
  NPrint "FontName = ", NPeek$(*a\Name), " ", *a\YSize
  NPrint "Style = ", *a\Style, ", FrontPen = ", *a\FrontPen, ", BackPen = ",
*a\BackPen
Else
  NPrint "ASL Font Requester cancelled."
EndIf


; *********************************************************
;             ...and the ASL Screen requester.
; *********************************************************

NResetTagList #ASLSM_InitialTopEdge , 14
      NAddTag #ASLSM_InitialLeftEdge, 20
      NAddTag #ASLSM_InitialWidth   , 300
      NAddTag #ASLSM_InitialHeight  , 200
      NAddTag #ASLSM_DoWidth        , 1
      NAddTag #ASLSM_DoHeight       , 1
      NAddTag #ASLSM_DoDepth        , 1
      NAddTag #ASLSM_DoAutoScroll   , 1
      NAddTag #ASLSM_DoOverscanType , 1

*b.NScreenInfo = NASLScreenRequest(TagList)

If *b
  Print "DisplayID = ", *b\DisplayID, " Width = ", *b\Width, " Height = ",
*b\Height, " Depth = ", *b\Depth
Else
  NPrint "ASL Screen Requester cancelled."
EndIf

NMouseWait
End

-- 
