Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: New Command Demo
X-UIDL: 993d90c7dac4a77d9414d55250370c01

Hello Roger
> Hi All Blitzer,
> 
> I would like that some of you tried this first part of a new
> PopUpMenuGadget library all written in ASM and, gimme back your
> appreciation.

It`s very nice, if a little classact/bgui`y (and I`m not a fan of either)

Only I found a bug. Because you are drawing directly on the screen,
I held the LMB down to open the list up and a miami window opened up
ontop of it... then... SPLAT! got a section of the window over the screen :(

Did you ever see that SDSGUI thing me, Dave and Booty started? It looked
very nice but was too slow. If you want the sources to have a look at
or continuw with, I`ll send it you.

> Using PopUpMenuGadget without MUI/BGUI/CLASSACT or Patch is now enable in
> Blitz Basic... our gui will have a better look!

Ours looked very nice!.. :) Shall I send you the sources?
I`d love to see a new GUI system appear (though ours wasn`t just a new
GUI system, it was new style windows and everything.)

> Roger Beausoleil
-- 

Rob,
