@NODE "Mail_511" "Newer DT-Picture Code"
From: Leigh Parry <lparry@free4all.co.uk>
Date: Fri, 03 Sep 1999 18:03:32 +0000
Subject: Newer DT-Picture Code
Encoding: binary
X-UIDL: 7e93304e8195f03b2c50d2ff2d4d6578

Hello,

I've done it again, uploaded a better version of the DT-Code

Now includes :-

DT-Picture functions v1.00 - 03-Sep-99

 Function DTLoad {OBJ.l,Fyle.s,RMap.l,Prec,Palet}
          - Load a DT-Image
 Statement ReleaseDT {OBJ}
          - Free the DT-Image
 Function BM_2_BM {*SrcB,SrcW,SrcH,*DestB,DestW,DestH}
          - Copy the DT-Image (with scaling)
 Function DT_2_BM {OBJ,bmap,nbmw,nbmh}
          - Copy the DT-Image into a (N)Bitmap (with scaling)

Also has an example prog, which loads a pic through DT's and when the window
is resized the picture automatically rescales the picture for output.
(Using System Bitmaps, Blitz Bitmaps or NBitmaps)
VERY QUICK 

- Get from website, better layout , archives split, so only 7k for above.

When I've got enough feedback I'll upload both DT-Function archives onto Aminet.
(Picture & Sound)

Should be the last update for a while.

I'm trying to do a function which can SAVE through the Datatypes, I'm only
just starting though. First tests don't look promising, so it may be a while.

Cya,

    Leigh.

