@NODE "Mail_523" "Re: NListview"
    25 Oct 99 12:51:20 +0100
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Mon, 25 Oct 1999 12:51:05 +0100
Subject: Re: NListview
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 9208df97520f8ac2d40095b1ee472d7e


> I want to convert one of my proggies over to use Fred's NCS libs.. but
> I am unsure how to detach a list and re-attach to a Nlistview type..
> Any ideas?
> 
> I need to detach the list, modify it, then re-attach it later?

Not sure if there's a dedicated NCS command, but you could do it with 
the one that sets the gadget attributes, and set the #GTLV_Labels tag 
to -1 and then reset it with the list. The OS command to use would be 
GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_, but I'm not sure of the NCS command.

To detach:

; Need to pass a pointer to your listview gadget and window.
; Would be NWindowID for the window, and probably the value returned
; by the command for creating the listview for gad
Statement Detach{gad.l, win.l}
  Dim tags.TagItem(2)
  tags(0)\ti_Tag = #GTLV_Labels,-1
  tags(1)\ti_Tag = 0
  GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_ gad,win,0,&tags(0)
End Statement


; Need to pass a pointer to your listview gadget and window.
; Would be NWindowID for the window, and probably the value returned
; by the command for creating the listview for gad
Statement Attach{gad.l, win.l, list.l}
  Dim atgs.TagItem(2)
  tags(0)\ti_Tag = #GTLV_Labels,
  tags(1)\ti_Tag = 0
  GT_SetGadgetAttrsA_ gad,win,0,&tags(0)
End Statement

To get the list parameter for the above function, you can use a piece 
of code like this:

; Check if there is an item in the list
If FirstItem(mylist())
  ; If there is, we get the address of first item in list
  ; (done with FirstItem) and then work back to the previous
  ; item in the list, which is the list header
  *fn.MinNode = &mylist() - Sizeof.MinNode
  list = *fn\mln_Pred
Else
  ; Otherwise we use 0 to show there is nothing to display
  list = 0
End If

You might also need to redraw the listview befoer the stuff gets 
displayed, after attaching it.


-- 
