@NODE "Mail_527" "Re: NTSC"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Sun, 05 Sep 1999 05:35:39 -0500
Subject: Re: NTSC
X-UIDL: 0f695b46f10f08b81f2a1a14e75dc3d5

Hi Vic

On 04-Sep-99, Vic E Babes wrote:
> Hello, NTSC users (probably Curt)
> 
> Two questions:
> 
> 1.  When should I use the FORCEPAL/GOPAL command for a program that uses
> Blitz mode?

Right at the beginning would be best, I think.
> 
> 2. Do I need to ensure that everything is computed before the vpos reaches
> 200, even when using Forcepal - in other words, I still only have 1/60th
> of a second each frame?

No, once you ForcePal it works just the same as on a PAL system.
The vblank rate becomes 50 - in other words, if it works on a PAL machine,
it will work the same on an NTSC machine forced into PAL mode...

The only catch is if the user's monitor can handle PAL modes - I don't think
it will work if the user has a TV instead of a real monitor...

Later...
-- 
OS/2 - half an operating system.

