Must be some continental/seasonal voodoo thing Tony, I discovered the same
thing just the other day ;]

I hurredly cut:

If something=somethingelse Then dosomething=donothing Else donothing=0

into

If something=somethingelse
  dosomething=donothing Else donothing=0
Else
  donothing=0
  NPrint "We're doing nothing!"
EndIf

And was baffled for a whole 5  minutes while I was wondering why it printed
that EVERY time no matter what =]

