> And was baffled for a whole 5  minutes while I was wondering why it printed
> that EVERY time no matter what =]

Reminds me of the old COBOL trick

If a not equal to 1 or 2
     always processed
else
     never processed
endif

because the if translates to 
if a not equal to 1 or a not equal to 2
which is obviously always true.

