@NODE "Mail_570" "Re: Palette-Request Request"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 28 Oct 1999 18:14:44 -0500
Subject: Re: Palette-Request Request
X-UIDL: 2f8adfde7e584766110dd0fd4fb05669

--BOUNDARY.1749392728.1

Hi Leigh

On 28-Oct-99, Leigh Parry wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> I would like to know if someone has been able to or suggest how to do a
> palette requester, but with only a few colours changeable.
> 
> E.G. On a 64 colour screen, I want a palette requester to come up but only
> to be able to change colours 13,14,15 & 16. If possible only having those
> colours in the requester.
> 
> Anyone got any ideas?

Here is an example I did a while back.

If you want to allow the user to alter the selected colour, just add 3
GTsliders, one for Red, Green, and Blue and link them to the selected
colour register.

Later...
-- 
All heiresses are beautiful.

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1749392728.1
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="GTTpalette.asc"

;make a GTpalette gadget that shows only colours 13 - 16
;and indicates the current selection as "depressed"

;You'll need amigalibs.res

;the Tag ColorOffset is the colour to start with
;the Tag NumColors is how many colours to show
;using -1 as IndicatorWidth cause the selected colour
;to be shown as a "depressed" button


WBenchToFront_
WbToScreen 0
Window 0,20,20,360,120,$8|$1000,"GT Palette test",0,1

GTTags #GTPA_ColorOffset,13,#GTPA_NumColors,4,#GTPA_IndicatorWidth,-1
GTPalette 0,51,20,20,300,40,"Select a colour",#PLACETEXT_BELOW,3

AttachGTList 0,0
Repeat
Format "##"  ;for showing the selected colour's register number
ev.l=WaitEvent
  If ev=$40
    Select GadgetHit
      Case 51
        selected.l=EventCode
        WLocate 132,80
        Print "Colour :",Str$(selected)
    End Select
  EndIf
Until ev=$200
End



--BOUNDARY.1749392728.1

