Hi

> The front-end for my game is in Blitz mode,but I want to load
> stuff.The problem is,I can't change to Qamiga and back 'cause they are
> compiler directives.. Here's what I mean: 

<snip>

> I tried Forbid_ (no imporovement) and OwnBlitter_(seemed to freeze
> up). Is there some way to stop other progs from using the blitter in
> qamiga mode? Or maybe increase my program's priority so that it goes
> faster?

The reason Forbid_ and OwnBlitter_ didn't do anything (or locked up) 
is because going into Blitz mode causes them to be called anyway. I 
think QAMIGA calls Permit_ but not DisownBlitter_, so you could try 
something like this (to do it manually):

Load stuff
BLITZ
Repeat 
  if key is pressed 
    Permit_
    Load more stuff
    Forbid_
    display it
  endif
Until Finished

-- 
