@NODE "Mail_656" "Re: Reading Mouse Buttons"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Wed, 8 Sep 1999 18:36:45 +0100
Subject: Re: Reading Mouse Buttons
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 01a3d8b4484045334ef2fc2c788578e6



> How can I check if either mouse button has been clicked on a screen? I just want
> to check if it has been pressed down once, it's being used for a game to fire a
> weapon and I want to avoid rapid fire if it's held down.

firing.w=0
.mainloop
repeat
	if joyb(0)>0 and firing=0 ; should work for left or right or left+right
		; Do stuff for fire weapon
		firing=-1
	end if

	if joyb(0)=0 then firing=0
until playerdies


