@NODE "Mail_663" "Re: Regarding NList w/ EFMUILib"
From: Rob Hutchinson <rob@satanicdreams.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Sep 1999 19:02:35 +0100
X-SenderInfo: 1; homepage="http://www.satanicdreams.com/"; dob=19071981
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: Regarding NList w/ EFMUILib
X-UIDL: 26c68aafc4e8f1f83b21a634732ceabd

Hello Andreas
>    Hello,
> 
> What seems to be the problem with using NLists in MUI using the EFMUILib
> that me and Erwan Fouret (lib coder) brought to the blitz world? I've used
> them in blitz without any problems. Included at the 2 included files with
> constants n stuff used for NLists and NListview. I have also included 3
> pictures of an email program that is partialy developed by me (only
> requires the actuall pop3/smtp functions), and it shows you that I've used
> the NList and NListview custom class.

You could have just said that you had used them, we beleive you :)

