@NODE "Mail_680" "Re: Rubber-band"
From: Rob Hutchinson <rob@satanicdreams.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Sep 1999 23:38:03 +0100
X-SenderInfo: 1; homepage="http://www.satanicdreams.com/"; dob=19071981
Organization: Satanic Dreams Software.
Subject: Re: Rubber-band
X-UIDL: bc8c46e6900869e2c803462e73e52f2b

Hello Curt
> Hi all,
> 
> When you "press" on the size gadget of a window and drag it around to
> re-size the window, Intuition draws a "rubber-band" as you go to show what
> the new size will be.

So it does.

> Does anyone know how to get the current size or co-ordinates of the
> rubber-band?
> While you are still moving, I mean, before you "release" the size gadget.

I really dont think that is possible, intuition suspends all other tasks
when you the drag or size gadgets of a window.

I`m not 100% sure though. Why do you need to get the size of the rubberband?
You cant do anything until it drops the window anyway.

> Thanks... 
> Later...
-- 

Rob,
