@NODE "Mail_681" "Re: Rubber-band"
From: James L Boyd <jamesboyd@all-hail.freeserve.co.uk>
Date: Sun, 26 Sep 1999 00:48:02 +0100
Subject: Re: Rubber-band
X-UIDL: bbaf9673291988126ce5d961c2ace6ef

Rob Hutchinson churned out *this* drivel:

>> Does anyone know how to get the current size or co-ordinates of the
>> rubber-band?
>> While you are still moving, I mean, before you "release" the size gadget.
> 
> I really dont think that is possible, intuition suspends all other tasks
> when you the drag or size gadgets of a window.

I'm nearly 99.9% sure you won't get that from the system, but you could
probably check what position (in the window) the mouse is at when you
click on the size gadget and keep track of the mouse's /screen/ position
from that point, then a little offset calculation should do the trick (?).

See ya,
