@NODE "Mail_692" "Re: Savebitmap shafted?"
From: "David McMinn" <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Organization: The Robert Gordon University, E&EE
Date: Tue, 7 Sep 1999 18:11:11 +0100
Subject: Re: Savebitmap shafted?
Encoding: 8bit
X-UIDL: 6ca5e227b51186441dbf60d33f48104a

> I dunno if I'm doing something wrong here, but is there bugs in
> Savebitmap and savepalette?

Bugs probably

> Is there any other commands/libs (like the one LoadIFF came
> from)  that can save an IFF pic to disk?

Mathias Parnaudeau released a small library (the IFFYouWantLib) that saves IFF 
files into animation frames, but it can also be used to save single IFF 
pictures with palette information. To get the archive, take a look in the 
Archives/libraries section of Blitz200 site (http://www.blitz-
2000.freeserve.co.uk).


