Hi James

On 09-Sep-99, James L Boyd wrote:
> ZimZum churned out *this* drivel:
> 
>> I dunno if I'm doing something wrong here, but is there bugs in
>> Savebitmap and savepalette?
> 
>> If I save bitmaps out from my program, they won't load back in to
>> another.. And PPaint, Dpaint, Fastview and Multiview (in fact any pic
>> viewer) crash when I try to load them in. So much for saving ILBMs....
> 
> I had this problem with shapes, but that was cos I wasn't saving the
> palette with it...
> 
> SaveBitMap #BitMap,Filename$[,Palette] 
> 
> If you haven't been saving the palette, that will probably fix
> it, otherwise...dunno...

Yes, I just checked.  As long as I include the palette, bitmaps and shapes
saved with the normal Blitz commands load fine into MultiView, PPaint,
Dpaint, Brilliance, and ImageFX.  Don't know about FastView - I don't have
it...

As far as the "SavePalette" command, it is meant only for saving palettes to
load back into a Blitz program...  To save a palette as an actual IFF
palette file, like you can with a paint program, use the RI "SaveCMAP"
command instead...

Later...
-- 


