Hi,there

I've done a bit of testing,and there definately _is_ something wrong with
SaveShapes (on my machine anyway).It seems that if the shape is wider than
(about) 100 pixels _and_ uses more than 5 bitplanes,then SaveShapes screws
it up.
I'm pretty sure it's not LoadShapes,'cause the exact same thing happens when
I DecodeShapes or CludgeShapes...

I've attached a quick test,could somebody make some shapes and run this
program? So that I can find out if it's just my copy of Blitz,or
something..
I have an A1200T 040-25/PPC-160 with 32MB.

I don't have the Blitz Support Suite,so I can't just use LEsaveshapes
(although I'd like to).Anyone got any suggestions?

Thanks for listening.
-- 
<sb>Geo

--BOUNDARY.1476829864.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="TestSaveShapes.ASC"


;SaveShapes Tester..
;All shapes tested are at least 200 pixels wide
;If the shape has 6 or more planes it seems to screw up..

LoadShape 0,"ram:200X100X3.bsh",0
LoadShape 1,"ram:200X200X4.bsh",1
LoadShape 2,"ram:250X250X5.bsh",2
LoadShape 3,"ram:350X350X6.bsh",3
LoadShape 4,"ram:350X350X8.bsh",4
LoadShape 5,"ram:200X400X7.bsh",5

SaveShapes 0,0,"RAM:0.shp"
SaveShapes 1,1,"RAM:1.shp"
SaveShapes 2,2,"RAM:2.shp"
SaveShapes 3,3,"RAM:3.shp"
SaveShapes 4,4,"RAM:4.shp"
SaveShapes 5,5,"RAM:5.shp"

LoadShapes 10,"ram:0.shp" ; this works
LoadShapes 11,"ram:1.shp" ; so does this
LoadShapes 12,"ram:2.shp" ; so does this
LoadShapes 13,"ram:3.shp" ; }
LoadShapes 14,"ram:4.shp" ; }-these don't
LoadShapes 15,"ram:5.shp" ; }

BitMap 0,640,512,8
Screen 0,0,0,640,512,8,$8004,"Test screen",1,2,0

For x=0 To 5               ;display each shape
 Repeat : Until Joyb(0)>0  ;judge for yourself if it's broken
 Cls 0
 Blit x+10,0,10 : ShowPalette x
 VWait 50
Next x

Repeat : Until Joyb(0)>0
End






--BOUNDARY.1476829864.2--




@ENDNODE
