Hi George

On 25-Oct-99, George Davis wrote:
> Damn! why can't anything be straight-forward?? >8( I have everything
> working (just about) and now I'll have to change it all 'cause Blitz has a
> bug..
> If I could just save _one_ blitz-format shape,at 200 x 400 x 7,everthing
> would be fine.. Couldn't I just dump the shape from memory...I expect not.
> I'm using DecodeShapes to get the shape out of the memory,is there a
> command in the BSS that can do this with LEshapes? I've been meaning to
> buy it for a while now...

Yes, there is a LECludgeShapes command, that will "unpack" one or more
shapes from memory, or that have been "IncBin"'d into your exec.

But, to be honest, I haven't actually tried LEShapes on such large sized
ones either...  I'll have to run a test to be sure - it may suffer the same
problems with large shapes...

> Thanks for helping me out,I guess I'll just have to try SaveShape and
> DecodeILBM,or something..

Well, if it's only ONE shape that size you need, how about this quick &
dirty hack:

Split it and save it out as two (or more) smaller shapes, then Blit them
side by side in your program?

Later...
