Yep i was having similar problems, but managed to sort this out with
the addition of the palette information.

The method i use for getting the view mode is shoddy to say the least,
but it works! ;)

ive attached the code i use :)

Hope this sorts out your problem :))

Chris.
-- 
                                    Chris "PrinceD" Deeney
                                  #chris@addnet.demon.co.uk#

                                       Powered by_
                                       ........./-\MIGA

                                 */#irc.dal.net amirc ungabunga#*/
                       +---------------------coding--------------------+
                       | *Powder Burnz*  | 0000159 lines | 003% complete |
                       +-----------------------------------------------+
                       |   *Critters*    | 0000465 lines | 050% complete |
                       +-----------------------------------------------+

--BOUNDARY.1749731608.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="savescreen.asc"

FindScreen 0

*scr.Screen=NPeekL(Addr Screen(0))
ScreensBitMap 0,0
Use Screen 0

scr_bitmap.l=*scr\BitMap
scr_width.w=*scr\Width
scr_height.w=*scr\Height
bmap_depth.b=*scr\BitMap\Depth

  numcols.w       = 2^bmap_depth

If CheckAGA
AGAPalRGB 0,(1 ASL bmap_depth)-1,0,0,0
Else
PalRGB 0,(1 ASL bmap_depth)-1,0,0,0
EndIf

  For i = 0 To numcols-1
    If CheckAGA
      AGAPalRGB 0,i,AGARed(i),AGAGreen(i),AGABlue(i)
    Else
      PalRGB 0,i,Red(i),Green(i),Blue(i)
    EndIf
  Next

mode.l=$8000+$4
If scr_width=320 AND scr_height=256 Then mode=$0
If scr_width=640 AND scr_height=256 Then mode=$8000
If scr_width=320 AND scr_height=512 Then mode=$4
If scr_width=1280 AND scr_height=512 Then mode=$20+$4

c=CSaveIff(0,f$,scr_width,mode,0)
CloseScreen 0
Free Palette 0
End

--BOUNDARY.1749731608.2--




@ENDNODE
