@NODE "Mail_716" "Re: ScreensPalette!?"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 05 Oct 1999 23:16:22 -0500
Subject: Re: ScreensPalette!?
X-UIDL: 7c5343ca757565bfc54c303cd759292d

--BOUNDARY.1748598256.2

Hi Chris

On 07-Nov-98, Chris Deeney wrote:

^^^^^^^^^^^^  Hmmm, I'm sure this just came in - it couldn't possibly have
been laying in my "in" folder that long...

> Hi guys,
> 
> Can any one tell me how to get the current screens palette and put it in
> a bb2 palette object so that i can save it with the screens bitmap?

Here you go...

You'll need amigalibs.res

Actually, you don't need the screen pointer stuff if you already know your
screen's depth...

-- 


                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/


--BOUNDARY.1748598256.2
Content-Disposition: attachment; filename="GetPalette.asc"

*scr.Screen     = Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
  scrDepth.w      = *scr\BitMap\Depth
  numcols.w       = 2^scrDepth

  Free Palette 0
  InitPalette 0,numcols        ;catch the screen's current palette
  For i = 0 To numcols-1
    If CheckAGA
      AGAPalRGB 0,i,AGARed(i),AGAGreen(i),AGABlue(i)
    Else
      PalRGB 0,i,Red(i),Green(i),Blue(i)
    EndIf
  Next


--BOUNDARY.1748598256.2

