@NODE "Mail_723" "Re: Sibly's on Phoenix"
 (envelope-from FlameDuck@software.dk)
Date: Sat, 16 Oct 1999 04:33:05 +0200
From: Mikkel =?iso-8859-1?Q?L=F8kke?= <FlameDuck@software.dk>
Subject: Re: Sibly's on Phoenix
X-UIDL: 2f43cd7fe76c6c8c99b2ccfbd30ab9bc

At 13:40 15-10-99 +0500, you wrote:

>>Wow, aint that spiffy.... not ;-)
>>That phoenix stuff is again an attempt at baking air :-)

>  Well, I thought that at first too, and it still remains to be seen.
>But with all the Amiga-knowledgeable people getting involved, they may
>have a chance to do something worthwhile.  Hmmm... We shall see.

I don't get it, what is it with AMiGA mentality ? Have we really reached a
level of self pity where we sit arround sobbing that no-one likes us
anymore ? Let's take iWin, they've had a rough time by any measures, what's
up with that ? As far as I can see Iwin is a win/win situation, it's not
like the AMiGA has a bright and shiney future anymore, okay ? ATM what do
we have ? Nothing, okay ? That how much the AMiGA's worth ATM, a big fat
zero. Shit I have an AMSTRAD CPC6128 right here that I can sell for more
than my A4000 ! Anyway along comes a company, telling us they have AMiGA
compatible machines that they can ship in a month or two, and what happens
? People give them a shit storm, it's a hoax, it's a joke... Right... SO
FUCKING WHAT IF IT'S A HOAX, you havn't lost anything, it's not like
they're gonna come and take away your AMiGA if you have a little faith in
other companies. And another thing, what would IWIN gain from lying to the
AMiGA public ? Nothing, so why should they, even if it is a hoax, someone
has spent time and money to create it, and I know AMiGA owners are
unnaturally paranoid, but this is just plain silly...

Then there's Phoenix, KOSH, UGN and everyone else trying to make a
difference, but no, why should we support them, I mean Phoneix is
unquestionably AMiGA, everyone that was at San Jose, who built the original
A1000, and who is still alive, is supporting it, why the hell can't we ?

I think the biggest joke of recent times, is how the media portraits "The
AMiGA Community", get out of here, there is no such thing okay ? The AMiGA
community is a collection of fractions, all with different oppinions of
which outdated technology should be used in the next AMiGA. We aren't a
community, we're just a bunch of losers sitting arround wondering why the
world was so cruel to us, and from where I'm standing it's no bloody wonder.

Sorry I sent this to the list, I know MOST people here are doing something
about the situation, and I salute every one of you, you deserve the highest
respect.


/FlameDuck/



@ENDNODE
