@NODE "Mail_736" "Re: Snap*!Shot!."
Sender: tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk
Date: Sat, 02 Oct 1999 17:21:33 +0100
From: Thomas Cobb <tdc98@doc.ic.ac.uk>
X-Accept-Language: en
Subject: Re: Snap*!Shot!.
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 23c130d65a4092ac7a3d5887c8d6d1e4

Chris Deeney wrote:

> hi guys!
>
> Can any one tell me (or give me source code) how to snapshot the currently
> used screen and save it as an iff with correct palette? ive been trying to
> do this but failed miserably - it's driving me crazy! ;)

Once you've got your screen then use:

ScreensBitmap 0,0
SaveBitmap 0,"File"

BUT!  I'm not sure if this is a bug in Blitz or not, but sometimes it really
messes up the picture. I think te problem is with interleaved screens - my
workbench comes out twice as wide and with extra bits down the side and
bottom.

    Thom


