> I have SuperTED v 2.24, and whenever I try to change the font in it, the
> screen closes, reopens and displays some wierd big font I never asked for.
> When I go back into prefs > font it says 'font not found'. I'm pretty much
> stuck with topaz.
>
> This is driving me nuts, I just got a big monitor and hi res 640x256 looks
> shit, but when I move up to 640x512, topaz is far too small to read
> properly.

I had that problem - I think you need to delete the old TED.PREFS from your
prefs drawer.  Even after fixing this, I still deleted Superted, because you
can only run one copy at once, and I use TED as my default text editor - you
can`t run SuperTed as a text editor at the same time as running it as a
Blitz editor.  But if you use a different text editor, you won`t have this
problem.

VIC E BABES





