@NODE "Mail_772" "testers wanted"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Tue, 05 Oct 1999 07:09:28 -0500
Subject: testers wanted
X-UIDL: 06f3f0651c483bb5a2b45454bfca3812

Hi Everybody,

I've now got (hopefully) the first release version of my picture-scaling
program ready.

For now, it only runs on the WB screen.

It loads and remaps any DataType image to a WB window, allows proportional
scaling with a slider, as well as the usual "half" & "double" gadgets and
also non-proportional scaling using the window's size gadget.  Also has
"Undo" and "Restore"

It now converts the loaded images to fast-ram chunkies, for minimum chip-ram
usage.
Chip-ram is still needed for the loading and saving functions...

You can save the whole window at any point as a standard .iff pic, as well
as grab and save .iff "bruhes" from the window.

Required: OS 3.xx, DataTypes installed for any image format you plan to use,
and ReqTools.  Some free fast-ram is also good, as it will probably be slow
otherwise.

It should be fine on all systems (ECS, AGA, and GFX-Cards) with the above
requirements.

Mail me direct if you wish to try it - if there are too many requests, I
will send it to the list.

And thanks again to everybody for their help, code, and ideas.

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/



