@NODE "Mail_797" "WritePixelArray8_ bug?"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Fri, 15 Oct 1999 05:35:39 -0500
Subject: WritePixelArray8_ bug?
X-UIDL: e7fe5668cbf33cae28a9e4fdd5ff410e

Hi Everyone,

I'm back with another strange problem...

I'm using the system function WritePixelArray8 to send the contents of a
chunky buffer to my program's window.  And I also use it to send the chunky
to a regular (Blitz) bitmap for saving to disk.

It works fine here, and on most of the tester's systems.

But some people report that they get a "blank" saved image (ie, the ilbm
file is the correct size and depth, but all pixels are colour #0).  Also,
one of them occasionally gets a blank window - but not always...

There is a patch on Aminet "NewWPA8", which says in it's doc that the
original "WritePixelArray8" command has a bug that can destroy the chunky
buffer.

Does anyone know anything about this bug?  The program runs fine on my
system with or without the patch...

Or, possibly, I am calling the command incorrectly.  But then, it shouldn't
work at all, on any system, would it?

Later...
-- 

                                    Yours electronically,
                                    Curt Esser
                                    camge@ix.netcom.com
                                    http://members.xoom.com/Curt_Esser/




@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_798" "Re: WritePixelArray8_ bug?"
 for blitz-list@netsoc.ucd.ie; Fri, 15 Oct 1999 19:09:32 +0100
From: "Vic E Babes" <zalda@home4968.freeserve.co.uk>
Subject: Re: WritePixelArray8_ bug?
Date: Fri, 15 Oct 1999 19:07:14 +0100
	charset="iso-8859-1"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 0b5ba564e95a891ca0c57999c65aec08

Hello, Curt,

> Does anyone know anything about this bug?  The program runs fine on my
> system with or without the patch...
>
> Or, possibly, I am calling the command incorrectly.  But then, it
shouldn't
> work at all, on any system, would it?
>

